  "texts": [
    "Finally, as this research aims to find the WCET of real-time robotic applications, the robotic concepts present in our case studies are explained.",
    "Quasi-Monte Carlo MethodsQuasi-Monte Carlo (QMC) methods are numerical integration techniques using low-discrepancy sequences, which distribute points more uniformly than random sequences.",
    "They reduce the integration error compared to traditional Monte Carlo methods, especially in high-dimensional spaces.",
    "This makes QMC methods valuable for evaluating multi-dimensional integrals in finance, physics, and engineering where precise computations are critical.",
    "The effectiveness of QMC is largely due to its use of sequences that ensure a more even coverage of the integration domain, enhancing computational efficiency and accuracy in applications requiring high-dimensional integration."
  ]
}